    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter April 25th with a primary objective of capitalizing on speed-driven upside, anchored by **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (82.12), who represents our strongest play of the day. Facing a favorable matchup against the struggling Roki Sasaki (5.52 xERA), **Pete Crow-Armstrong** benefits from a massive 19% boost in SP skill-based projection and a 14% platoon edge, making him a must-start despite the lower batting order slot. Following closely is **Junior Caminero** (73.53) and **Trea Turner** (68.86). **Junior Caminero** remains a high-floor asset against the mid-rotation stability of Ober, while **Trea Turner**\u2014our primary engine for SB scarcity\u2014holds an elite 68.86 score, buoyed by a 10% premium for hitting at the top of the order against Bryce Elder.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision involved **Victor Scott II**, who just missed the cut with a 39.50 score, falling narrowly below our 40.0 floor. While we value the elite sprint speed **Victor Scott II** brings to the table, the combination of a tough outing against Brandon Woo (3.30 xERA) and an unfavorable 9th-order slot made it prudent to keep him on the bench to preserve our game caps. Conversely, we are aggressively starting **Kyle Schwarber** (65.76) and **Colt Keith** (62.83). **Kyle Schwarber** continues to be a lock thanks to his elite 0.402 xwOBA, while **Colt Keith** leverages a significant 7% platoon advantage against Singer.\n\nStrategic risks remain as we navigate the \"Lineup Pending\" status for several key contributors like **Gary Sanchez**, **Dillon Dingler**, **Colt Keith**, **Trea Turner**, **Hyeseong Kim**, **Kyle Schwarber**, **Josh Smith**, **Yordan Alvarez**, and **Pete Crow-Armstrong**. We are monitoring these shifts closely, particularly the impact on **Hyeseong Kim**, whose output is sensitive to the 63% SB-hold probability of the opposing battery. While **Christian Yelich** and **Lars Nootbaar** remain sidelined on the IL, and **Zac Veen** continues his development in the minors, we are confident in the active depth provided by **Caleb Durbin** (57.26) and **Kazuma Okamoto** (57.12) to keep us competitive across all five roto categories today.",
